Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan and bring to the boil. When
boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp} and the @ground turmeric{1%tsp}, stir in the
@jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid on the pan. Leave
to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the
rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g} then chop them into thirds. Roughly chop
the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a #frying pan on high heat. When the oil is hot, add
the @British pork mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a
#wooden spoon to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Once the mince is browned, add the @red Thai style paste{50%g}, @coconut milk{200%ml}
and @water for the curry{50%ml}, and stir to combine. Add the green beans,
bring to the boil and then simmer until the sauce has reduced and the green
beans are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While everything finishes off have a quick tidy up. Once cooked, taste the
curry and add @salt and @pepper if you feel it needs it.

Divide the turmeric rice between #bowls{}, and top with the curry. Sprinkle on
the coriander. Enjoy!

> If you've opted for pork mince instead of beef mince, just cook the pork mince
> in the same way the recipe tells you to cook the beef mince in the step above
> and in the rest of the recipe.